    "The authors also reported that one adult with ID opted out of social media in self-imposed digital exclusion due to 'worry and fears about possible risks' (n.p.)",
    "and another opted out of Facebook use due to a friend's negative experience 'he was on Facebook and he had threatened, threatened message … and that's why I don't like about it … I can't trust it.",
    "I don't like it' (n.p.).",
    "Unwanted Contact and 'Weird' Content As a participant with communication disability reported in Caron and Light [21], 'the worst thing about social media is sometimes people use it inappropriately.",
    "Some people use it to pick on others and to make them feel hurt."
